# Server half (`server/`)

When working in `server/`, read and follow:

@server/CLAUDE.md

Data contract source of truth: `server/src/models/*.model.ts` — **ignore** stale `server/src/models/schema.md`.

## Quick reminders

- Stack: Express 5 + TypeScript + Mongoose (MongoDB) + Google Gemini.
- Deploy target: Render (free tier — cold-starts are normal).
- Run tests: `cd server && npm test` (offline, in-memory Mongo, mocked Gemini).
- Live AI smoke: `cd server && npm run test:ai` with `RUN_AI_TESTS=true` and real `GEMINI_API_KEY`.
- Git commands only inside `server/` — it is its own repo.
- **Golden Rule 2:** never add `protect` to AI or public-content read paths; use `optionalAuth` where needed.
